From: tawc
Origin: own

Drop the AOSP-only `nativewindow` Rust crate dep from
src/gfxstream.rs's PLATFORM_AHB export path. The crate is the
Rust binding to libnativewindow.so vendor APIs (specifically
AHardwareBuffer_getNativeHandle), only published inside AOSP, so
rutabaga doesn't build outside AOSP with the gfxstream feature.

Our bridge does its AHB handoff on the C++ side via
exportColorBufferMemory() (notes/gfxstream-bridge.md, "Zero-copy
buffer sharing" Option A). export_blob() with handle_type =
PLATFORM_AHB isn't on that path. The patched function returns
InvalidResourceId so a future code path that exercises this
branch fails clean rather than silently.

